===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|thurghfare|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} *{{term||þurhfaru|a thoroughfare, passage through|lang=ang}}, suggested by {{term|þurhfaran||to go through, go over, traverse, pierce, pass through, pass beyond, transcend, penetrate|lang=ang}}, equivalent to {{prefix|thorough|fare}}. Compare also {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|þurhfær||an inner secret place|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Durchfahrt||passage through, thoroughfare|lang=de}}. More at {{l|en|thorough}}, {{l|en|fare}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# That through which one goes; a place of travel or passage.
# [[passage|Passage]]; [[travel]]; [[transit]].
#: ''Hell and this world, one realm, one continent / Of easy '''thoroughfare'''.'' ― Milton.
# a [[road]] open at both ends, especially one with much [[traffic]].
# a [[passage]] such as a [[waterway]] that has heavy traffic.

